                                         JOHANNESBURG - A 19-year-old Limpopo man has been arrested for allegedly raping a 64-year-old woman. It’s alleged that the suspect is the victim’s nephew. The police’s Moatshe Ngoepe says the man grabbed and throttled the elderly woman until she fell unconscious and subsequently forced himself onto her. “The SA Police Service in Limpopo condemns in the strongest possible terms violent attacks perpetrated against the elderly people. The arrested suspect will appear before the local magistrate on Monday on a charge of rape.”